headline: Will Kraft Heinz’s Breakup And Mixed Q3 Results Change Kraft Heinz’s (KHC) Narrative
summary: Kraft Heinz recently reported third-quarter 2025 results showing a 2.3% decline in net sales and an 18.7% drop in adjusted EPS, while still topping analyst expectations. At the same time, the company unveiled plans to split into two separate businesses, effectively unwinding its 2015 merger to sharpen focus and capital allocation.
